    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[FGKMT18] Ford, Kevin and Green, Ben and Konyagin, Sergei and Maynard, James and Tao, Terence, Long gaps between primes. J. Amer. Math. Soc. (2018), 65-105.\n \n [Iw78] Iwaniec, Henryk, On the problem of {J}acobsthal. Demonstratio Math. (1978), 225--231.",
      "remarks": "That $h(k)\\ll k^2$ is a conjecture of Jacobsthal. Iwaniec \\cite{Iw78} proved\\[h(k) \\ll (k\\log k)^2.\\]The best lower bound known is\\[h(k) \\gg \\frac{(\\log k)(\\log\\log\\log k)}{(\\log\\log k)^2}k,\\]due to Ford, Green, Konyagin, Maynard, and Tao \\cite{FGKMT18}.\n\nThis is a more general form of the function considered in [687]."
    },
