  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $h(k)$ be Jacobsthal's function, defined to as the minimal $m$ such that, if $n$ has at most $k$ prime factors, then in any set of $m$ consecutive integers there exists an integer coprime to $n$. Determine the order of magnitude of $h(k)$. In particular, is it true that\\[h(k) \\ll k^2?\\]",
